      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:8:1:37:18",
      "text": [
        " مَا كَانَ شَيْ‏ءٌ أَحَبَّ إِلَى رَسُولِ اللَّهِ (صلى الله عليه وآله) مِنْ أَنْ يُظِلَّ خَائِفاً جَائِعاً فِي اللَّهِ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473293\">H 14619</a> – Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham and someone else, who has narrated the following:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-a\">A</span>bu Abdullah</span><sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There was nothing more beloved to the Rasool Allah<sup>saww</sup> than to remain fearful and hungry for the Sake of Allah<sup>azwj</sup> Mighty and Majestic’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "171. Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham and someone else, who has narrated the following: Abu Abdullah (a.s.) said: ‘There was nothing more beloved to the Rasool Allah (saww) than to remain fearful and hungry for the Sake of Allah (azwj) Mighty and Majestic’."
        ]
      }
